description: Performs 10 mc runs at integer undersampling point in the grid of half-width 0.1 around predicted undersampling point, with james stein denoiser. Sparsity varies in [0.005, 0.05] in interval of 0.005. No. of rows varies in [1000] and no. of columns is [3, 4, 5, 10, 15, 20, 30, 50]. cov(Resid.T) used to estimate the noise covariance at each iteration instead of resid.T * resid/n.
